DOCUMENT();
loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
"MathObjects.pl",
);
 
Context("Numeric");

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(2,9,1);
# $b = random(1,5,1);
$b = list_random(qw(a b c r s));

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT
Evaluate exactly, using the Fundamental Theorem of Calculus:
$BR
\( \int_0^{$b} $a e^x dx = \) \{ ans_rule(35) \}

END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

ANS( fun_cmp( "$a*(e^($b) - 1)", 'var'=>[$b,'x'] ) );

Context()->texStrings;
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR SOLUTION $PAR

The derivative of \(e^x\) is \(e^x\), so an antiderivative of \($a e^x\)
is \($a e^x\), and we get 
\[ 
\int_0^{$b} $a e^x dx = $a e^x\big|_0^{$b} = $a e^{$b} - $a e^0 = 
  $a e^{$b} - $a.
\]

END_SOLUTION
Context()->normalStrings;


COMMENT('MathObject version');
